Here's the PlantUML component diagram for the NVMe SSD Automation Test Framework:

```plantuml
@startuml yuwen123441_NVMeAutomation

[Test Cases] as TC
[Test Suites] as TS
[Common Library] as CL
[NVMe ioctrl Library] as NIL
[Driver] as D
[Dynamic Library] as DL
[Logic Layer] as LL
[Data Structures] as DS
[Buffer Management] as BM

interface "OS ioctl interface" as IOCTL
interface "NVMe Device" as NVME

TC --> TS
TS --> CL
CL --> NIL
CL --> LL
LL --> D
D --> DL
DL --> IOCTL
IOCTL --> NVME

LL --> DS
LL --> BM
D --> DS
D --> BM

note right of TC
  Implement and execute SSD 
  functionality verification
end note

note right of CL
  High-level Python interfaces 
  for Admin, I/O, and buffer management
end note

note right of NIL
  Low-level interaction with 
  system's driver layer
end note

note right of D
  Python wrapper around 
  dynamic C library
end note

note right of DL
  C interface to kernel 
  NVMe driver for ioctl calls
end note

note right of LL
  Higher-level abstraction for 
  NVMe device interaction
end note

note right of DS
  Define Python data structures 
  for NVMe commands, queues, 
  and log pages
end note

note right of BM
  Provides Buffer class for 
  memory management
end note

@enduml
```